{"lemma":"أَرِيكَة","slug":"أَرِيكَة","root":"#.ر.ك","root_slug":"_-ر-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ر-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n621"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sofa"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"throne","examples":[{"text":"جَلَسَ المَلِكُ عَلَى أَرِيكَتِهِ","english":"the king sat on his throne"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Unknown, suggested as Iranian, comparing with Classical Persian اورنگ (awrang, “throne”), but this is difficult. A native origin would connect the Arabic only to أَرَاك (ʔarāk, “toothbrush tree”), or perhaps an obsolete أَرَكَ (ʔaraka, “to persevere, to bide”), because it is a place of abode, which however likely derives from the plant name, as these trees are inviting for camels, goats, and humans to eat."},"ipa":["/ʔa.riː.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n621","headword_ar":"اَرِيكَةٌ","root":"Ark","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A raised couch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariyr","text_ar":"سَرِير"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajalap","text_ar":"حَجَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, and Jel in xviii. 30,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is a tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pavilion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"byt","text_ar":"بيت"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adorned with cloths and curtains,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of curtained canopy"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alcove"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for a bride;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel ubi suprà;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a raised couch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sryr","text_ar":"سرير"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajalap","text_ar":"حَجَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and having before it a curtain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"when alone, not thus called: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing spread upon the ground to sit or lie upon, in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajalap","text_ar":"حَجَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Zj, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a raised couch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sryr","text_ar":"سرير"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absolutely, whether in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hjlp","text_ar":"حجلة"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or [in the CK “ and ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything upon which one reclines such as is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariyr","text_ar":"سَرِير"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnaS~ap","text_ar":"منَصَّة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaA$","text_ar":"فِرَاش"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) or [in some copies of the K “ and ”]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a raised couch"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sryr","text_ar":"سرير"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ornamentally furnished and decorated, in a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pavilion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~ap","text_ar":"قُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a chamber,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an apartment,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or by this may be meant here"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tent of any kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"though I think that in this instance it more probably denotes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an inner apartment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an alcove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which, when there is not in it a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sryr","text_ar":"سرير"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hajalap","text_ar":"حَجَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Sgh, K:) accord. to Er-Rághib, so named because"},{"kind":"page_break","n":51},{"kind":"text","text":"originally made of [the wood of] the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAk","text_ar":"اَرَاك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or because it is a place of abode; from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arak biAlmakaAni","text_ar":"اَرَك بِالمَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ be abode in the place: ” (TA:) pl"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araAy^iku","text_ar":"اَرَايِكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and [coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ariykN","text_ar":"اَرِيكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Zj","K","S","Sgh"]}]}}